To start git 

- git init 


Add files to git staging 
- git add filename (addes only the file )
-git add --all (addes all files)
-git add . (addes all)

To Commit something 
- git commit -m "messages"


To see all command 
- git log 
-git log --oneline (shows in oneline)

To see user config details on git 
- git config --list 

To see the difference between commits 
- git diff (shows what has been added but not commited)
-gitdiff id 
--git diff head  (present to previous)

To github repository
- git remote add origin https://github.com/UrmeJaman/reponame.git
- git branch -M main
-git push -u origin main

Branching 
-git branch branchname

change branch 
-git checkout branchname 
- git checkout -b branchname (create+change to it)

push to git repo 
- git push 
- git push --set-upstream origin branchname( to different branch )


Remove file from git 
-git rm filename

-git clean -f  (delete)
-git clean -g -n (give an allert)

Removing Branch 
-git branch -d branchname(local)
-git push origin --delete remoteBranchName(remote)

Removing last pushed commit
-git revert id

Keep a flag 
- git stash
-git stash push/apply
-git stash pop

Remote to local 
-git clone/git pull
-git fetch

Add all branch to main 
-git merge 

